                    <h3>Grilled Chicken Fajitas</h3>
                    <p>Marinated grilled chicken, saut√©ed onions and bell peppers, served with warm flour tortillas, sour cream, and salsa.</p>
                </div>
                <p>In the content-box model, the width and height of an element only include the content area, and do not include the padding, border, or margin.</p>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2>Border-Box Model Example</h2>
                <div class="border-box">
                    <h3>Crispy Fish Tacos</h3>
                    <p>Beer-battered cod, shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, and tartar sauce, served in a crispy corn tortilla.</p>
                </div>
                <p>In the border-box model, the width and height of an element include the content area, padding, and border, but not the margin.</p>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2>Padding Example</h2>
                <div class="padding-example">
                    <h3>Roasted Vegetable Soup</h3>
                    <p>A hearty soup made with roasted vegetables, beans, and aromatic spices, served with a swirl of creamy yogurt.</p>
                </div>
                <p>The padding property adds space between the content area and the border.</p>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2>Border Example</h2>
                <div class="border-example">
                    <h3>Grilled Steak Frites</h3>
                    <p>Grilled ribeye steak, served with crispy fries and a side of garlic aioli.</p>
                </div>
                <p>The border property adds a border around the content area.</p>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2>Margin Example</h2>
                <div class="margin-example">
                    <h3>Chicken Caesar Salad</h3>
                    <p>Romaine lettuce, grilled chicken, croutons, and parmesan cheese, tossed in a tangy Caesar dressing.</p>
                </div>
                <p>The margin property adds space between the element and other elements.</p>
            </section>
        </main>
